ispersion ($\\sigma_{int}$) to the KDS dynamical mass budget by adopting a\n'total' effective velocity of form $V_{tot} = (Vc^{2} +\n4.0\\sigma_{int}^{2})^{0.5}$. The rotation-dominated and dispersion-dominated\nKDS galaxies fall on the same locus in the total-velocity versus stellar-mass\nplane, removing the need for debate over the precise selection threshold for\nrotation-dominated galaxies. The comparison sample offsets are in the range\n+0.08 to +0.15 dex in total-velocity zero-point (-0.30 to -0.55 dex in\nstellar-mass zero-point) from the local Tully-Fisher relation at z > 1,\nconsistent with steady evolution of the ratio of dynamical to stellar mass with\ncosmic time.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 9 Nov 2017 21:06:11 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 13 Nov 2017 11:09:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-11-15"}
